<i>adverb</i>: 쾌히 [쾌히], 즐거이 [즐거이], 유쾌히 [유쾌히], 맛깔스레 [맏깔스레] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>쾌히 [쾌히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pleasantly</dd><br>
<dd>즐겁고 신이 나게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a happy and excited manner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. completely</dd><br>
<dd>앓던 질병이 다 나아 건강한 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In a healthy state after recovering from a disease.</dd><br>
<dd>3. readily; without hesitation</dd><br>
<dd>말과 행동이 머뭇거림 없이 시원하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Without hesitation in one's speech and action.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>즐거이 [즐거이]</dt><br>
<dd>pleasantly; delightfully</dd><br>
<dd>마음에 들며 흐뭇하고 기쁘게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a happy and delightful manner.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>유쾌히 [유쾌히]</dt><br>
<dd>pleasantly</dd><br>
<dd>즐겁고 상쾌하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a happy and refreshed manner.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>맛깔스레 [맏깔스레]</dt><br>
<dd>1. palatably; toothsomely</dd><br>
<dd>음식이 맛이 있게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of tasting good.</dd><br>
<dd>2. palatably; pleasantly</dd><br>
<dd>마음에 들 만큼 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of so good as to suit one's fancy.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>